member.returns:
Each element can be either a byte array or a number:
if it's a byte array (encoded text), the operator shows text glyphs;
if it's a number (glyph adjustment), the operator inversely adjusts the next glyph position by that amount (that is: a positive value reduces the distance between consecutive glyphs).

members.member:
Renders this content context into the specified rendering context.

@param context Rendering context.
@param size Rendering canvas size.
@since 0.1.0

member.remarks:
It displays text directly on the page. Unlike an ordinary text annotation,
                a free text annotation has no open or closed state;
                instead of being displayed in a pop-up window, the text is always visible.

                  It represents a particular view of a document, consisting of the following items:


the page of the document to be displayed;

the location of the document window on that page;

the magnification (zoom) factor to use when displaying the page.

member.summary:
Document's conformance version is mandatory;
                      any unsupported feature is forbidden and causes an exception
                      to be thrown in case of attempted use.

member.returns:
How the first argument compares to the second:


-1, smaller;

0, equal;

1, greater.

How the first argument compares to the second:


-1, smaller;

0, equal;

1, greater.

How the first argument compares to the second:


-1, smaller;

0, equal;

1, greater.

member.summary:
Gets the identifier components:


the first one is the primary code. It can be any of the following:


a 2-character ISO 639 language code (e.g., en for English);

the letter i, designating an IANA-registered identifier;

the letter x, for private use;



the second one is the first subcode. It can be any of the following:


a 2-character ISO 3166 country code (e.g., en-US);

a 3-to-8-character subcode registered with IANA (e.g., en-cockney)

private non-registered subcodes;



subcodes beyond the first can be any that have been registered with IANA.
